cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.AR, cs.SY

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the downlink and uplink of cellular networks and proposes a new paradigm for network throughput, outage, and power consumption. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 

2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the changes needed in current mobile systems to enable downlink/uplink decoupling, which involves information transmission and processing. 

3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the increase in mobile data usage, which includes multimedia content such as video and audio. 

4. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper discusses the changes needed in current mobile systems to enable downlink/uplink decoupling, which may involve changes in hardware architecture. 

5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a new paradigm for cellular networks, which involves system design and control.
